[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The term of art for this is "pajama time" (also called "work outside of work" in the formal literature). The studies have names for it and measure it; Christine Sinsky's work at the AMA found that for every hour physicians spend face-to-face with patients, they spend nearly two additional hours on EHR and desk work (Sinsky CA, Colligan L, Li L, et al. "Allocation of Physician Time in Ambulatory Practice: A Time and Motion Study in 4 Specialties." Ann Intern Med. 2016;165(11):753-760). A separate way to say the same thing: for every hour physicians spend face-to-face with patients, they spend roughly two hours in the EHR.
